-- Bugs Fixed and Ready For Release 
Added: Option to turn off landscape captured progress backdrop
Added: Changed progress backdrop to use textures rather than pixel drawing (speedup on some cards)
Added: Moved the player id of the single player spectator to allow stats user 1 to connect online
Added: Scorched client supports remote game connection initiated via .s3l file
Added: Option to turn off real-time object shadows to improve framerate

Fixed: Applied some small patches to help cross platform compilation
Fixed: Support for wxWidgets 2.8 added
Fixed: Disconnects caused by players having invalid PNG files
Fixed: Optimized OpenGL state changes to improve framerate
Fixed: Aimed over tag so it generates particles with the correct power
Fixed: Roller collisions to make them less sensitive
Fixed: Roller strength to make them less powerfull against shields

-- Bugs in current development release
Dvorak keyboard support is broken
Crashing when minimized during texture/level load

